    <img src="http://www.mediacurrent.com/sites/default/files/imagecache/thumb_blog_spotlight/5keytakeaways.png" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-thumb_blog_spotlight imagecache-default imagecache-thumb_blog_spotlight_default" width="200" height="150" /> <p>As a flexible system, Drupal is constantly being adapted to a variety of situations. Regional Drupalcamps and user groups provide an interesting perspective on how Drupal easily takes on a unique local flavor. At the local <a href="http://www.meetup.com/louisianadrupal/">Louisiana Drupal Users Group meetups</a>, for example, we often discuss Drupal-powered restaurant sites. At CapitalCamp, held July 26-27 at George Washington University in Washington D.C., Drupal's powers and popularity in the public sector were on full display.</p>
<p>Here are five useful things I learned at CapitalCamp.</p>
